Football Match Attendance Prediction using Machine Learning

Overview

This project uses Machine Learning techniques to analyze historical football match data and predict stadium attendance. The system applies both unsupervised learning (K-Means Clustering) and supervised learning (Random Forest Regression) to identify patterns and forecast match attendance.

Dataset

The dataset contains information about football matches such as:
	•	Home team and away team
	•	Match scores
	•	Team performance statistics
	•	Ticket prices
	•	Attendance numbers
	•	Match conditions

Only numerical features are used for machine learning analysis.

Methodology

1. Data Preprocessing
	•	Load dataset using Pandas
	•	Select numerical columns
	•	Remove missing values
	•	Scale the data using StandardScaler

2. Exploratory Data Analysis

A correlation matrix is generated to understand relationships between variables.

3. K-Means Clustering

K-Means clustering is applied to identify hidden patterns in match demand.
Matches are grouped into three clusters representing different attendance levels.

4. Random Forest Model

A Random Forest Regressor is trained to predict match attendance using historical data.

5. Model Evaluation

The model performance is evaluated using:
	•	R² Score – measures how well the model explains attendance variation
	•	RMSE – measures prediction error
	•	F1 Score – evaluates classification accuracy for attendance categories

Results

Example model results:
	•	R² Score: 0.686
	•	RMSE: 3258 spectators
	•	F1 Score: 0.80

These results show that the model can reasonably predict football match attendance.

Applications

This system can help football clubs:
	•	forecast stadium attendance
	•	optimize staffing and security planning
	•	improve ticket pricing strategies
	•	enhance fan experience

